narratives.question_text: Were the resources available to you - library, fabrication labs, classroom, software, desk space, etc. adequate for the fulfillment of the assigned work?  If not, please make suggestions.
comments: It is a bit annoying that the art history classroom doesn't access our school's network. That room in general is pretty depressing.

The facilities were sufficient for what I was doing, although it would have helped to have a more established or dedicated space for mold-making and casting. The metal shop isn't quite the right place for using plaster and cement, not to mention not having a good place to clean up afterwards.
